5:
...And having saved the kingdom,
the brave champion set forth on
a new adventure. But that is a story
for another time.
8:
Heroes are so awesome! Guess what
I'm gonna be when I grow up?
11: Not if you don't study more.
16:
Well, the champion wielded magic,
didn't he? And you can't hope to
use magic if you don't attend to
your studies.
22:
Oh, isn't it? ...Now, that's enough
excitement for one day. You'll have to
come back if you'd like to hear more.
And be careful on your way home.
24:
Okaaay... I can't wait until next time!
Bye, Yuwel!
28:
I never knew you were such
a gifted storyteller.
32:
It isn't me. It's this book. My mother
gave it to me when I was young.
34:
I was a sickly child. When I couldn't
go outside, these tales and pictures
kept me company.
37:
They're about a champion, right?
I know he and I aren't the same person
but I almost feel... self-conscious.
40:
Really? I see you reflected in
every page of this book, Sir Light.
42:
...The children need something
to hope for. Even if that something
is a distant dream.
45:
All great deeds begin with a dream.
May I return for your next reading?
54:
Ah right... Alk asked me to pick up
a few things for supper.
57:
Excuse me.
I'd like a few of those pump... kins...
64: Yuwel! What are you doing here?
67:
Well... I'm buying supper.
So... you have your own shop now.
69:
Oh. Yes. There's, er... no place for me
back home at the moment, so
thought I'd settle here for bit and
earn a spot of money.
70:
And I don't hate being a merchant!
Not at all. It's a good feeling, knowing
you're helping honest folks feed their
friends and family. Think this was
my calling, actually.
71:
...Not that I regret taking up the sword.
Oh, me and my big mouth.
Now I've gone and made you feel bad.
77:
Now, I'd like couple of pumpkins,
a pound of chickpeas, and handful of
those herbs.
80:
These ones over here?
They're mighty pungent.
84:
We have a capable chef, Will.
He'll be the one cooking, not me.
89: So, how much do I owe you?
91: It all comes out to thirty-two gold, sir.
99:
Then market price is too much.
Give me a discount, won't you?
For old time's sake.
101:
Oh, fine. I'll lower it to thirty,
but no less.
104:
Come now. You can make it twenty
for a friend, can't you?
107:
Aw, you wouldn't turn your "friend" into
a beggar, would you? Twenty-eight,
and that's my last word on the matter.
111: Very well. Twenty-eight it is then.
116:
There's going to be a gathering soon.
A whole lot of us from the
Swallow Knights. Won't you come and
let everyone know how you're doing?
119: Of course, Will. I'll be there!
